  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The corneal collagen cross-linking treatment has been used with increasing success to treat
      corneal dystrophies such as &quot;keratoconus.&quot; Recent advances have allowed different techniques
      for performing this cross-linking treatment. This study investigates the effects of corneal
      cross-linking using different surgical techniques.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
